---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About -- JZ Stafura"
  description="Cognitive psychologist and researcher based in Pittsburgh, PA. PhD from the University of Pittsburgh; work in language comprehension, applied statistics, and organizational measurement."
>

  <section class="hero">
    <p class="overline">About</p>
    <h1>Joseph Z. Stafura, Ph.D.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Cognitive psychologist. The numbers follow the questions. Pittsburgh, PA.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio">
    <div class="bio-main">
      <p>I'm a cognitive psychologist with a career built at the intersection of rigorous measurement, applied statistics, and real organizational problems. My PhD training at the University of Pittsburgh placed me in Charles Perfetti's Language and Literacy lab, where I studied how the brain builds meaning from text. That work spanned theoretical models of reading comprehension, EEG/ERP studies of word-to-text integration, and the mechanisms that separate skilled from less-skilled readers. That foundation shapes everything I do: I care about how things actually work, not just whether they appear to work.</p>

      <p>After graduate school, I co-founded Affective Health, a digital assessment and behavior change platform that grew to serve 16,000+ users across academic and applied settings. The platform drew on Ecological Momentary Assessment methodology, capturing experience closer to when it happens rather than relying on recall. That work produced measurable outcomes: 15-16% improvements in key performance constructs, across more than 20 client engagements totaling over $1M in projects.</p>

      <p>I currently manage research administration for the Learning Research and Development Center at the University of Pittsburgh: a $50M+ portfolio of grants from NIH, NSF, IES, DOD, and major private foundations. The work demands the same thing the rest of my career has: translating complex, multi-stakeholder data into decisions that hold up under scrutiny.</p>

      <p>JAB Lab is my independent research operation. Projects outside the day job: D3 visualizations, AI hallucitation studies, violence research dashboards, and whatever I'm currently absorbed in.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bio-links">
      <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=F6LcYIoAAAAJ&hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Scholar &nearr;</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jzstafura" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn &nearr;</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/jzstafura" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub &nearr;</a>
      <a href="https://jzstafura-lab.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JAB Lab &nearr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="overline">Education</p>
    <div class="entries">
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2018</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Ph.D., Psychology</h3>
          <p class="entry-sub">Cognitive Neuroscience Concentration &middot; University of Pittsburgh</p>
          <p class="entry-body">Dissertation on cognitive processes during reading, completed in Charles Perfetti's Language and Literacy lab. Research at the intersection of language comprehension, memory, and word learning, using EEG/ERP and behavioral methods. Core contributions: situation model-based integration in coherent discourse, memory and prediction at sentence boundaries (Stafura &amp; Perfetti, 2014; Stafura, Rickles &amp; Perfetti, 2015), and biphasic interference in word learning (Fang, Perfetti &amp; Stafura, 2017). Co-authored the most-cited paper in reading comprehension theory, 2011-2020 (Perfetti &amp; Stafura, 2014). 7 peer-reviewed empirical papers; 2,000+ citations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2007</div>
        <div>
          <h3>B.A., Psychology &amp; English Literature</h3>
          <p class="entry-sub">Summa Cum Laude, 4.0 GPA &middot; SUNY Purchase College</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="overline">Experience</p>
    <div class="entries">
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2022&ndash;Present</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Fiscal Specialist IV (Pre- &amp; Post-Award)</h3>
          <p class="entry-sub">Learning Research and Development Center &middot; University of Pittsburgh</p>
          <p class="entry-body">Managing ~60 active grants totaling $50M+ in external funding across 20+ PIs. Pre-award processing for ~80 federal and non-federal proposals per year (NIH, NSF, IES, DOD, Gates, Spencer). Analytics and decision support for budget development, compliance risk, and resource allocation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2018&ndash;2023</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Instructor, College of General Studies</h3>
          <p class="entry-sub">University of Pittsburgh</p>
          <p class="entry-body">Cognitive Psychology, Cognitive Psychology Lab, Research Methods.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2013&ndash;2023</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Co-Founder &amp; Chief Cognitive Scientist</h3>
          <p class="entry-sub">Affective Health / The Affective Computing Company &middot; Pittsburgh, PA</p>
          <p class="entry-body">Co-designed and product-managed a cloud-based digital experience platform. Led analytics for 16,000+ users across 20+ client engagements. Applied EMA methodology to organizational performance measurement. Grew company from zero to ~$1M ARR.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="overline">Technical Skills</p>
    <div class="skills-grid">
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h4>Statistics &amp; Methods</h4>
        <p>GLM tradition &middot; Experimental design &middot; Factor analysis &middot; Regression &middot; A/B testing &middot; EMA methodology &middot; Behavioral &amp; electrophysiological methods</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h4>Programming &amp; Data</h4>
        <p>Python (pandas, numpy, scipy, scikit-learn) &middot; R &middot; SAS &middot; SPSS &middot; SQL &middot; MATLAB &middot; Git</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h4>Visualization &amp; Tools</h4>
        <p>D3.js &middot; matplotlib &middot; seaborn &middot; Jupyter &middot; Excel (advanced) &middot; Power BI &middot; SharePoint</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="overline">Selected Publications</p>
    <div class="entries">
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-meta">2014</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Perfetti &amp; Stafura</h3>
          <p class="entry-body">Most-cited paper in reading comprehension theory, 2011-2020. Multiple articles and chapters with 50+ citations; 2,000+ total citations.</p>
          <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=F6LcYIoAAAAJ&hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="entry-link">Full publication list &nearr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .overline {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

.bio {
  padding: 3rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
  overflow: hidden;
}

  .bio-main p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .bio-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .bio-links a {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bio-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .entries {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 7rem 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .entry-meta {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .entry h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .entry-sub {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .entry-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .entry-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

.skills-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 2rem;
  padding-top: 1.5rem;
  overflow: hidden;
}
  .skill-group h4 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .skill-group p {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .bio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  .entry { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.25rem; }
  .entry-meta { padding-top: 0; }
  .skills-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
